display(Markdown(r'## example 1'))
h = 1.3e-6
d = 17e-3
D = 1609
H = '?'
s = r'\quad \frac{H}{D} = \frac{h}{d} \Rightarrow' 
s += r'\frac{h}{d} \cdot D'
s += r'= \frac{4 \cdot 1.3 \cdot 10^{-6}}{17 \cdot 10^{-3}} \cdot 1609 \approx %g cm' % (round(4*h*D/d *100, 1))
display(Math(s))
display(Markdown(r'$\Rightarrow$ can be viewed'))

example 1¶

$\displaystyle \quad \frac{H}{D} = \frac{h}{d} \Rightarrow\frac{h}{d} \cdot D= \frac{4 \cdot 1.3 \cdot 10^{-6}}{17 \cdot 10^{-3}} \cdot 1609 \approx 49.2 cm$

$\Rightarrow$ can be viewed

display(Markdown('## example 4'))

def circle(img, center, radius):
    img = img.copy()
    for i in range(img.shape[0]):
        for j in range(img.shape[1]):
            if (i-center[0])**2 + (j-center[1])**2 <= radius**2:
                img[i, j] = 255
    return img

img_cir = circle(cam_img, (20, 110), 10)
plt.imshow(img_cir, cmap='gray')
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

example 4¶
